commit.message:
Update Ledger Nano S, S+ et X

The tokens have a pinpad.
Add Ledger Stax
Add NXP Pegoda 3
Add FujitsuTechnologySolutions GmbH Dual Smartcard Reader D321

INSTALL: add instructions to install from git repo

Signed-off-by: Martin Dummer <martin.dummer@gmx.net>
Move ACS ACR1281U from "should work" to "unsupported"

Release 1.5.5

Signed-off-by: Ludovic Rousseau <ludovic.rousseau@free.fr>
supported_readers: change order betweeen Gemalto and GEMALTO
Update to PCSC 2.0.1
Add Imprivata USB CCID

Kapelse: simplify code

Move the standard cases with the other USE_COMPOSITE_AS_MULTISLOT cases.

USE_COMPOSITE_AS_MULTISLOT: reset static_interface on error

If a composite reader fails to load all the CCID interfaces then the
reader will be unloaded. We must reset the interface counter so that the
next reader will be handled correctly.

The Kapelse Kap-Link2 always has 3 CCID interfaces

No need to have a complex code or check config_desc->bNumInterfaces

Set num_CCID_interfaces values for Kapelse readers

We must set both values num_CCID_interfaces & max_interface_number for
USE_COMPOSITE_AS_MULTISLOT to work as expected.
Add comments about Kapelse readers
ccid_usb.c: Kapelse code reformat

Simplify the code for USE_COMPOSITE_AS_MULTISLOT

No need to check again which readers are composite since if a reader is
composite the value of max_interface_number has been set a few lines
earlier in the code.
COMPOSITE_AS_MULTISLOT : Add Kapelse readers

COMPOSITE_AS_MULTISLOT: Avoid code duplication using num_interfaces

Add a new field num_interfaces to _ccid_descriptor structure to store
the number of CCID interfaces of a composite USB device.

configure: replace "case in" by AS_CASE() M4 macro

- RDR-80x86AKU WAVE ID Plus
- RDR-7x16AKU WAVE ID Nano Reader (USB-A)
- RDR-7xU6AKU  WAVE ID Nano USB-C Reader

interface is not supported.
